description:
Smart Zombies, Part 1 of 2

While in the middle of the apocalyptic ruins of a major city, our Chaos Trio seeks refuge from nightfall inside a large luxury hotel. But there's already a community of scientists inside! Though welcoming, these scientists hold a secret that will change everything we thought we knew about the zombie apocalypse. Welcome to the first issue of the game changing Act 2!
name: Smart Zombies, Part One of Two

description: Comic Shop News is comics' weekly newsletter. Each issue is full-color, 8-12 pages in length, and features CSNsider, news, and interviews. CSN has a complete monthly checklist (complete with PREVIEWS item codes), plus exclusive CSN Hot Picks, 'Fab Firsts,' and a monthly checklist of all the first issues for the month!

Wendy is now attached to a functioning body and brain, and Jason's life seems perfect. Wendy is cute, attentive, and possesses a love of both ice cream and good books; she's Jason's perfect mate. Unfortunately, Jason chose a chassis that once belonged to his sister's best friend. Even worse: Wendy appears to have an unhealthy affinity for sharp objects, and an even stronger desire to protect her secret -- at any cost.

Faustia's bipolar reign of terror continues. Will Mercy be able to change the tide, or will she have to take up residence and "move back in with mom" to save the world? There's not enough bourbon in the universe!

description:
One of the most groundbreaking Marvel Comics of all is collected for the first time! Born to be the world's most fearsome fighter, Shang-Chi's life takes a major turn when he discovers the truth about his father, the villainous Fu Manchu! So begins the epic story of the Master of Kung Fu! On a quest to end the reign of his pernicious patriarch, Shang-Chi pits his deadly hands and furious feet against incredible foes like Tiger-Claw, Razor-Fist, the mysterious Midnight - and even the macabre Man-Thing! But will his mastery of martial arts be enough in a throwdown with the Amazing Spider-Man? Collecting SPECIAL MARVEL EDITION #15-16, MASTER OF KUNG FU (1974) #17-37, GIANT-SIZE MASTER OF KUNG FU #1-4, GIANT-SIZE SPIDER-MAN #2 and material from IRON MAN ANNUAL #4.

Collects Special Marvel Edition #15-16, Master of Kung Fu #17-37, Giant-Size Master of Kung Fu #1-4, Giant-Size Spider-Man #2 and material from Iron Man Annual #4.

description: Fueled by the powers of the Teenomicon, Frank the Lesser Demon banishes Kit, Moon,and Belle to the worst place he can think of: the Central Offices of the Nexus. There, the kids must team up with one of their very first enemies in order to find a way to escape the Nexus Offices. Meanwhile, Toulouse and Moon's Great Aunt Esther devise a way to take down Frank and save the brainwashed citizens of Showside. Can the kids battle their way through the hordes of office demons determined to make them work 9 to 5?

The Immortal Brijit's first attempt to capture the Wraithborn power did not go as planned, but She has power over the living as well as the dead, and new followers are always easily found. Meanwhile, Melanie finds an unexpected ally.

Tenma and Oto are now dating for real instead of being in an engagement arranged by their parents. This changes everything in their relationship—talking on the phone every other day, meeting up on days other than the 20th of each month... Oto's making an effort to move on with her life, regardless of Haruto's unsaid feelings for her. But when she runs into him and Megumi at the amusement park together, Megumi proposes a double date...
name: Chapter 28
